org.jcvi.jillion.assembly

Interface AssembledRead

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Rangeable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AceAssembledRead, AsmAssembledRead, CasPlacedRead, TasmAssembledRead, TigrContigRead
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AceAssembledReadAdapter, DefaultAssembledRead, DefaultCasPlacedRead

    public interface AssembledRead
extends Rangeable
    A AssembledRead is a read that has been assembled and placed at a particular location in its assembly. The location is relative to the object this read has been assembled into (ex Contig or Scaffold etc).
    Author:
    dkatzel

      • getDirection

        Direction getDirection()
        Get the Direction that this read is relative to the contig this read was placed in. If the read is Direction.REVERSE then the NucleotideSequence of this read has already been reverse complemented so that it matches the consensus.
        Returns:
        either Direction.FORWARD or Direction.REVERSE.

      • toGappedValidRangeOffset

        long toGappedValidRangeOffset(long referenceOffset)
        Convert the given zero based reference offset into the equivalent gapped valid range offset on this read. For example if this read starts at consensus offset 100 then toGappedValidRangeOffset(100) will return 0.
        Parameters:
        referenceOffset - the zero based reference offset.
        Returns:
        equivalent gapped valid range offset on this read.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if referenceOffset is not covered by this read.
        See Also:
        toReferenceOffset(long)

      • toReferenceOffset

        long toReferenceOffset(long gappedValidRangeOffset)
        Convert the given zero based gapped valid range offset into the equivalent gapped reference offset on the reference. For example if this read starts at consensus offset 100 then toReferenceOffset(0) will return 100.
        Parameters:
        gappedValidRangeOffset - zero based gapped valid range offset.
        Returns:
        the equivalent zero based gapped reference offset as a long.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if gappedValidRangeOffset < 0 or ≥ this read's length
